article.description: Kareem South had 21 points as Texas A&M-Corpus Christi topped Houston Baptist 76-69 on Saturday. Emmanuel Toney added 20 points for the Islanders. Toney also had six assists for the Islanders.
article.headline: South carries Texas A&M-CC past Houston Baptist 76-69
article.linkText: South carries Texas A&M-CC past Houston Baptist 76-69
article.story: CORPUS CHRISTI, Texas -- Kareem South had 21 points as Texas A&M-Corpus Christi topped Houston Baptist 76-69 on Saturday. Emmanuel Toney added 20 points for the Islanders. Toney also had six assists for the Islanders. Jashawn Talton had 19 points for Texas A&M-Corpus Christi (14-17, 9-9 Southland Conference). Jake Babic added 10 points and eight rebounds. Ian DuBose had 28 points and seven rebounds for the Huskies (12-17, 8-10). Braxton Bonds added seven rebounds. The Islanders leveled the season series against the Huskies with the win. Houston Baptist defeated Texas A&M-Corpus Christi 73-72 on Feb. 2. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
